Demonstration of basic predefined datatypes

In this case MPI_INT. But there are others

    MPI_CHAR,
    MPI_FLOAT, MPI_DOUBLE

There are also

    MPI_INT8_T, MPI_INT16_T, MPI_INT32_T, MPI_64_T (similar to stdint.h)
    MPI_REAL, MPI_REAL2, MPI_REAL4, MPI_REAL8, MPI_REAL16

and some more ...

Note that these are not the actual types, they are simply macros that
differentiate types.
